  "market_context": "ES printed a bearish daily closure, signaling continuation lower. On the 4-hour chart, price retraced into a fair value gap sitting in the lower half of the bearish daily range, providing a higher-time-frame point of interest from which to anticipate further downside delivery.",
  "key_observation": "After the 4-hour candle swept the prior high and closed back inside the range (bearish closure into the FVG), dropping to the 15-minute revealed a protected high formed by a closure through the series of up-close candles, enabling a refined short entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify a bearish daily closure on ES, establishing bias for continuation lower.",
    "Step 2: On the 4-hour chart, locate a fair value gap in the lower half of the bearish range as the point of interest where price could retrace before continuing down.",
    "Step 3: Wait for 4-hour candles to play out; confirm a bearish closure that sweeps the prior high and closes back inside the range.",
    "Step 4: Drop down to the 15-minute chart to find a protected swing high, identifying the series of up-close candles that built that high.",
    "Step 5: Confirm price has closed through that series of up-close candles, validating the protected high.",
    "Step 6: Anticipate the protected high remains intact; on a new sweep into a POI, look for another closure through the up-close candles to form a fresh protected high for entry.",
    "Step 7: Target sellside liquidity below as the draw on liquidity for the continuation move."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Use higher-time-frame bias (daily bearish closure) and a 4-hour POI (fair value gap) to frame the trade, then refine entries on the 15-minute via protected swings confirmed by closures through opposing candle series. Stops sit above the invalidation; targets are sellside liquidity.",
